# flow.word — what a FLOW is, a conditional word. A being's quality, the word that gives
# it its able each moment. Descends from word.word, can.word, able.word, being.word, the verbs.
# The host eval loop is seed/present/ables/flow.js. A flow is pure: same moment, same able.
# `pass`, `play`, `stack`, `test` are grounded here, the conditional's verbs. This is the Word's
# colon at home, a when then a able.

A flow is a being's quality, the conditional word that gives it its able.
A flow has clauses, in order. A clause has a able, and may have a when.
A when tests the moment — the caller, verb, act, space, the being, a fact's order in its chain, and the content a fact carries — by equals, in, more, less, or present, with and, or, not.
A when reads no clock. Order is the chain's; a time is only content a fact already has.
A clause with no when always passes. A clause with one passes only when its when is true.
When a clause passes, the clause gives its able only if the able asks no cognition, or the cognition it asks is the being's. Otherwise the clause drops, and the flow goes on.
When a being is granted a able whose words can in this space, or the able is a seed its nature has: the being can play it.
The first passing clause that does not stack is the primary. A clause that stacks gives its words on top of the primary, not in its place.
A flow folds to one able, the primary's name and voice with the words of all that stack.
A caller may name a able when it calls. When the being can play it, it is the primary, and the flow gives only what stacks.
When no clause gives a primary, the being's default able is the primary. When none can, there is no primary able. The fold yields only what stacks, or nothing.
The able a flow folds is the moment's, signed into its act.
A flow is a pure word. The same moment folds the same able.
